cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.SE. 

This paper is about a query language for NoSQL databases, which are typically used for storing and querying semi-structured data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper mentions the computational capabilities of the language. The paper also discusses the syntax and semantics of the language, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper mentions experimental validation, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
